       xml:id="sec-rmt-tools-systemd">
   <info>
      <title>RMT <systemitem class="daemon">systemd</systemitem> commands</title>
   </info>
   <para>You can manage RMT-related services with the standard <systemitem class="daemon">systemd</systemitem> commands. The RMT server has the following services and timers:</para>
   <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
         <term>
            <command>rmt-server.target</command>
         </term>
         <listitem>
            <para>A <systemitem class="daemon">systemd</systemitem> target that starts all required RMT components.</para>
         </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
         <term>
            <command>rmt-server.service</command>
         </term>
         <listitem>
            <para>The RMT server.</para>
         </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
         <term>
            <command>rmt-server-migration.service</command>
         </term>
         <listitem>
            <para>This service migrates the database to the newest schema, if required. There is no need to manually interact with this service.</para>
         </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
         <term>
            <command>rmt-server-sync.timer</command>
         </term>
         <listitem>
            <para>This timer is responsible for periodically synchronizing all repository product data from the SUSE Customer Center.</para>
         </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
         <term>
            <command>rmt-server-mirror.timer</command>
         </term>
         <listitem>
            <para>This timer is responsible for periodically synchronizing all RPMs from the SUSE Customer Center.</para>
         </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
   <para>Use <command>systemctl</command> to manage the RMT services and timers.</para>
</sect1>
